---
folder: architectures
id-format: "NNNN-kebab-slug.md"
---
## Purpose
Cluster-wide decisions and structural constraints (ADR-flavored): how services are
exposed, how GitOps flows, hardware/capacity trade-offs, network topology. NOT per-service
detail (→ services/) and NOT a specific outage (→ incidents/), though a recurring incident
often reveals an architectural weakness worth recording here.

## File template
Frontmatter: `id`, `title`, `status`, `created`, `updated`, `links`.
Body:
- `## Context` — the forces at play; what problem or constraint prompted the decision.
- `## Decision` — what was chosen, concretely.
- `## Consequences` — what this makes easy, and what it costs.
- `## Constraints honored` — verified facts the decision must respect (port ranges,
  cert SANs, NFS root_squash, node capacity, etc.).
- `## Alternatives considered` — what was rejected and why (keep — it prevents relitigation).

## Retro rules
Extract decisions with lasting consequence: exposure mechanism (Cloudflare vs Tailscale
operator vs Ingress vs hostNetwork), GitOps branch/sync model, storage-class choice,
capacity/placement strategy. Update when a decision is revisited; mark `superseded` and
link the successor rather than deleting. Record verified external/system constraints even
when they didn't change a decision — they shape future ones.

## Cross-linking
Referenced by `[[services/NNNN]]` (which follow the decision) and `[[incidents/NNNN]]`
(which exposed the constraint); links to `[[runbooks/NNNN]]` that operationalize it.
